snippet: The backup quarterback for the Quakers, Andrew Holland, picked up where the injured Billy Ragone left off, and Penn clinched at least a share of the Ivy title.
abstract: Pennsylvania defeats Harvard, 30-21, to clinch at least a share of their third Ivy League football title in last four years.
lead_paragraph: The backup quarterback for the Quakers, Andrew Holland, picked up where the injured Billy Ragone left off, and Penn clinched at least a share of the Ivy title.

headline.seo: Ragone Is Injured, but Penn Puts Away Harvard
headline.main: Penn, Fueled by Injury, Gains Share of Ivy Title
headline.print_headline: Penn, Fueled By Injury, Gains Share Of Ivy Title
